    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter #28387 title might be truncated even when it fits in the width.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the following 'init-float-title.lua' file:\n\n    ```lua\n    local title = 'abcde'\n    local config = {\n      relative = 'editor',\n      row = 1,\n      col = 1,\n      height = 3,\n      width = vim.fn.strchars(title),\n      border = 'single',\n      title = title,\n    }\n    vim.api.nvim_open_win(vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true), false, config)\n    ```\n\n2. `nvim --clean -u init-float-title.lua`. Observe that the title is `<bcde`, although `abcde` fits.\n\nThis root cause is probably #28387.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFloating window title is not truncated if it can fit full into available width.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1783+ged9abb1851\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this exact functnionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.17.9-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.3-arch2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
